other_tests.procedure_name: CT Abdomen and Pelvis with Contrast
other_tests.findings: Dilated, fluid-filled appendix in the right lower quadrant measuring 8 mm with surrounding fat stranding and mucosal hyper-enhancement compatible with appendicitis. An appendicolith noted in the appendiceal tip. No evidence of perforation, abscess, free air, or ascites. Normal findings in the liver, gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, kidneys, urinary bladder, prostate, and osseous structures.
